ARCHITECTURE QUALITY ASSESSMENT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Dimension                         Status    Notes
--------------------------------  --------  ------------------------------------
API surface clarity               POOR      10-arg function; app_name mismatch
Module separation of concerns     POOR      All logic in one 223-line file
Processor pipeline design         PARTIAL   Fixed chain; no extension hooks
Configuration model               POOR      Module-level side effect at import
Enricher extensibility            POOR      Hard-coded; requires signature change
Dependency hygiene                PARTIAL   httpx/loguru should be optional/removed
Error propagation strategy        PARTIAL   warnings.warn not visible in prod
CLI completeness                  POOR      Exposes < 10% of library options
Test isolation                    PARTIAL   Global structlog state leaks between tests
Performance at scale              POOR      Loguru reconfigured per logger creation

OVERALL ARCHITECTURE SCORE: 4 / 10

The library's concept is sound and the public API is clean at its core.
The most impactful single change is moving structlog.configure() out of module
scope (ARCH-001) — this unblocks multi-configuration support, proper test
isolation, and makes visionlog a well-behaved guest in any Python application
that also uses structlog. The second most impactful is clarifying and likely
removing loguru (ARCH-002 / DEP-001), which would eliminate an entire class of
performance and correctness issues.

